President Obama will host the second White House Science Fair on February 7th. The event will showcase the winners of various science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) competitions from across the country. The President will also announce initiatives aimed at helping more students excel in math and science and earn degrees in these subjects. The fair will feature exhibits of student work, including research and inventions. The President will deliver remarks highlighting the importance of STEM education to the country's economic future. This event follows the first White House Science Fair held in 2010 as part of the President's Educate to Innovate campaign. The President has previously met with winners of the Google Science Fair and made surprise appearances at other science fairs.